## Naming Convention — Project Code

Every Meta Ad **headline** must begin with a fixed project code in square brackets:

```
[MV_ICITY] Mountain View iCity — Lake View Units
[MRG-LUSAIL] Lusail Residence — Flexible Payment Plans
```

**Why:** Campaign names and Ad IDs are unreliable — one project may have many campaigns over time. The Project Code is fixed and controlled entirely by Ramy at ad creation, not generated by Meta.

**How it works in n8n:**

```
Inspect Referral (headline)
    ↓
Code node: regex /^\[(.+?)\]/
    ↓
Project_Mapping (Google Sheet: Project Code → Folder ID)
    ↓
Google Drive (project folder)
    ↓
Project_Bible.md + Sales_Playbook.md
    ↓
OpenAI context
```

**Hard rule:** Any new ad without a Project Code in the headline cannot be reliably identified by MAYA and must be corrected before going live.

